<p><b><a name="ricin_definition_and_facts" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>*Ricin definition and facts medically edited by: <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/script/main/art.asp?articlekey=81326" rel="bio" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk')">John P. Cunha, DO, FACOEP</a></p>.<p><b><a name="what_is_ricin_and_where_does_it_come_from" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="how_soon_do_poisoning_symptoms_start_and_how_long_does_death_take" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="how_much_ricin_is_lethal" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>Ricin works by getting inside the cells of a person's body and preventing the cells from making the proteins they need. Without the proteins, cells die. Eventually this is harmful to the whole body, and death may occur.</p>.<p><b><a name="how_you_could_be_exposed_to_ricin_and_how_deadly_is_it" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="what_is_ricin_used_for" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>Ricin is found in the byproducts of castor oil production. It is a protein. Unfortunately, it is used as a biological weapon and by assassins.</p>.<p><b><a name="is_there_a_treatment_antidote_or_cure_for_ricin_poisoning" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="what_should_i_do_if_ive_been_exposed_to_ricin" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="how_do_authorities_confirm_cases_of_suspected_ricin_poisoning" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="where_can_i_get_more_information_about_ricin" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>You can contact one of the following:</p>.<p>Regional <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/poison_control_centers/article.htm" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');" rel="dt">poison control</a> center: 1-800-222-1222</p>.<p>Centers for Disease Control and Prevention</p>